    <field name="abstract_teim">This collection consists of a photostat copy of Samuel Chester Reid's petition to Congress for the establishment of a line of telegraphs from New York to New Orleans.  Additional items include programs from the 1956 dedication of the Samuel Chester Reid Monument in Brooklyn's Green-Wood Cemetery, as well as a transcript of a speech given by Charles S. Thomas, Secretary of the Navy, at the ceremony.  A map of Green-Wood Cemetery marking the location of the Reid monument is also included.</field>
